ah -- I don't know if you all have figured out the code style for that yet, but normally for type annotations i'd stick them directly against the return type (since they're effectively type use annotations), so a method with type and method annotations would look something like:
@Override
public @Nullable Boolean blah() {
    return /* blah */;
}

